00057 void test()
00058 {
00059     // create some data, f(x) = abs(5-(x-2))
00060     FrequencyData fd;
00061     FrequencyData::container& data = fd.data();
00062     for (int i=-5; i<=5; i++)
00063         data.push_back(FrequencyDatum(i+2, 5-abs(i)));
00064     fd.analyze(); // recache after changing data
00065 
00066     // verify peak()
00067     FrequencyData::const_iterator max = fd.max();
00068     unit_assert(max->x == 2);
00069     unit_assert(max->y == 5.);
00070 
00071     // verify stats
00072     unit_assert(fd.mean() == 25./11);
00073     unit_assert(fd.meanSquare() == 85./11);
00074     unit_assert(fd.sumSquares() == 85.);
00075     unit_assert_equal(fd.variance(), 85./11 - 25.*25/11/11, 1e-12);
00076 
00077     // write out data
00078     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename1 << endl;
00079     fd.write(filename1, FrequencyData::Text);
00080 
00081     // read into const FrequencyData
00082     string filename2 = "FrequencyDataTest.output2.txt";
00083     FrequencyData fd2(filename1, FrequencyData::Text);
00084 
00085     // verify normalize()
00086     fd2.normalize();
00087     unit_assert(fd2.shift() == -2);
00088     unit_assert(fd2.scale() == 1./5);
00089     max = fd2.max();
00090     unit_assert(max->x == 0);
00091     unit_assert(max->y == 1.);
00092 
00093     // verify transform(shift, scale)
00094     fd2.transform(-fd2.shift(), 1./fd2.scale());
00095 
00096     // verify read/write
00097     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename2 << endl;
00098     fd2.write(filename2, FrequencyData::Text);
00099     diff(filename1, filename2);
00100 
00101     // test subrange
00102     string filename3 = "FrequencyDataTest.output3.txt";
00103     FrequencyData fd3(fd2, fd2.data().begin(), fd2.max()); // copy first half
00104     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename3 << endl;
00105     fd3.write(filename3, FrequencyData::Text);
00106     FrequencyData fd4(fd2, fd2.max(), fd2.data().end()); // copy second half
00107     ofstream os(filename3.c_str(), ios::app);
00108     fd4.write(os, FrequencyData::Text);
00109     os.close();
00110     diff(filename1, filename3);
00111 
00112     // read/write binary, and metadata
00113     fd.scanNumber(555);
00114     fd.retentionTime(444);
00115     fd.calibrationParameters(CalibrationParameters(1,1));
00116     fd.observationDuration(666);
00117     fd.noiseFloor(777);
00118     string filename4a = "FrequencyDataTest.output4a.txt";
00119     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename4a << endl;
00120     fd.write(filename4a, FrequencyData::Text);
00121     string filenameBinary1 = "FrequencyDataTest.output1.cfd";
00122     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filenameBinary1 << endl;
00123     fd.write(filenameBinary1);
00124 
00125     FrequencyData fd5(filenameBinary1);
00126     unit_assert(fd5.observationDuration() == 666);
00127     fd5.observationDuration(fd.observationDurationEstimatedFromData());
00128     unit_assert(fd5.scanNumber() == 555);
00129     unit_assert(fd5.retentionTime() == 444);
00130     unit_assert(fd5.observationDuration() == 1);
00131     unit_assert(fd5.noiseFloor() == 777);
00132     if (os_) *os_ << "Calibration: " << fd5.calibrationParameters().A << " " << fd5.calibrationParameters().B << endl;
00133 
00134     string filename4b = "FrequencyDataTest.output4b.txt";
00135     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename4b << endl;
00136     fd5.write(filename4b, FrequencyData::Text);
00137     diff(filename4a, filename4b);
00138     fd.calibrationParameters(CalibrationParameters());
00139 
00140     // test window
00141     FrequencyData window1(fd, data.begin()+1, 2);
00142     FrequencyData window2(fd, fd.max(), 1);
00143     FrequencyData window3(fd, data.end()-2, 2);
00144     string filename5 = "FrequencyDataTest.output5.txt";
00145     if (os_) *os_ << "Writing " << filename5 << endl;
00146     ofstream os5(filename5.c_str());
00147     window1.write(os5, FrequencyData::Text);
00148     window2.write(os5, FrequencyData::Text);
00149     window3.write(os5, FrequencyData::Text);
00150     os5.close();

00155 void testFind()
00156 {
00157     const FrequencyData fd(filename1);
00158 
00159     FrequencyData::const_iterator it = fd.findNearest(-.2);
00160     unit_assert(it!=fd.data().end() && it->x==0);
00161 
00162     it = fd.findNearest(.2);
00163     unit_assert(it!=fd.data().end() && it->x==0);
00164 
00165     it = fd.findNearest(6.1);
00166     unit_assert(it!=fd.data().end() && it->x==6);
00167 
00168     it = fd.findNearest(7.1);
00169     unit_assert(it!=fd.data().end() && it->x==7);
00170     
00171     it = fd.findNearest(666);
00172     unit_assert(it!=fd.data().end() && it->x==7);
00173 
00174     it = fd.findNearest(-666);
00175     unit_assert(it==fd.data().begin());
00176 }

00179 void testAddition()
00180 {
00181     FrequencyData fd(filename1);
00182     FrequencyData fd2(filename1);
00183 
00184     fd += fd;
00185 
00186     for (FrequencyData::const_iterator it=fd.data().begin(), jt=fd2.data().begin(); 
00187          it!=fd.data().end(); 
00188          ++it, ++jt)
00189         unit_assert(it->y == 2.*jt->y);
00190 
00191     fd2.transform(0, -2.);
00192     fd += fd2;
00193 
00194     for (FrequencyData::const_iterator it=fd.data().begin(); it!=fd.data().end(); ++it)
00195         unit_assert(it->y == 0.);
00196 }

00220

00222

00224     ofstream temp(filename.c_str());

00226     temp.close();
00227

00230

00232     if (os_) *os_ << "result: " << result << endl;

00234 
00235     // test noise floor calculation on sample mass data 
00236 
00237     FrequencyData fdMasses;
00238     CalibrationParameters cp = CalibrationParameters::thermo();
00239 
00240     for (RawMassDatum* p=sampleMassData_; p!=sampleMassData_+sampleMassDataSize_; ++p)
